The paper discusses Capsule Networks, which are a type of machine learning model that falls under the categories of deep learning and neural networks. The paper specifically focuses on the inner routing procedures of Capsule Networks, which involves modeling the agreement between capsules. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since Capsule Networks are a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses natural language processing tasks, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category as well.
